Reference

Main functions

add_species()

Add species to a ForestGEO-like dataframe of census data.

add_equations()

Add allometric equations to a census dataset.

allo_evaluate()

Evaluate equations, giving a biomass result per row.

allo_find()

Get default equations of each type.

allo_lookup()

Look up in allodb information about each equation_id.

allo_order()

Find the best equations given a priority order.

Helpers

complement()

Complement a dataframe with rows from another dataframe.

reduce_complement()

Reduce a list of dataframes row-binding each dataframe in a given order.

Internal functions that flag issues to be fixed

fixme_find_duplicated_rowid() fixme_pick_one_row_by_rowid()

Handle multiple rowids: find duplicates and pick a single row.

Other internal objects to hidden or remove

bad_eqn_id()

Find equations that can't be evaluated.

default_eqn()

Restructure equations from allodb.

.bad_eqn_id

Character vector giving equation_id of equations that can't be evaluated.

.default_eqn

Dataframe of default equations, restructured from allodb.
